# Private Sales Methodology Overlay

> Copy this file to `context/sales-methodology-overlay.md`. The copied file is private and ignored by Git. Check with whatever your employer allows before adding real qualification criteria, stage names or process detail here, even to a private, gitignored file; some organisations restrict this regardless of where it lives.

This overlay lets you map your own approved qualification or sales method onto the workflows already in this repository, so a workflow like pipeline evidence review or objection handling can use your language and your criteria instead of guessing generic ones. It does not change any public workflow file, and nothing in it is ever committed.

## How to Mark Each Field

Every field below needs one of two labels, not just a value:

- `evidence required`: this can only ever be filled from something the customer, or a confirmed internal source, actually said or provided. An AI assistant should never infer or guess this one, no matter how likely it seems.
- `judgement call`: a reasonable assessment a salesperson may make even without a direct customer statement (for example, "does this stakeholder behave like a champion"), but it stays labelled as judgement, never treated as a confirmed fact.

Getting this distinction right matters more than filling in every field. A method with three well-labelled fields is more useful here than ten fields with no label at all.

