## Your Stage Names

> If your employer allows it, list your own pipeline stage names here so a workflow can use your language instead of a generic placeholder like "Qualification" or "Proposal Sent." A plain description of what each stage means is enough; leave out whatever triggers an automated stage change in your CRM if that is considered confidential.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## What This Overlay Actually Changes

This file does not alter any workflow in the public repository. When you ask an AI assistant to run a workflow that involves a qualification judgement or a pipeline stage (pipeline evidence review, objection handling, a business case), point it to this file so it uses your method and stage language instead of a generic one or an invented one. It should still keep the same evidence-versus-judgement distinction the public workflows already use; this overlay changes the vocabulary, not the discipline.

## Never Commit This

Do not add `context/sales-methodology-overlay.md` to a commit, pull request or public repository.

Before publishing a change, check that Git still ignores it:

```text
git check-ignore -v context/sales-methodology-overlay.md
```
